For those of you still don't know which is Puke and which is Snot, we 
thoughtfully provide you with a page of frequently asked questions about the 
act, the performers, and the reasons why they do what they do. Or make up 
your own and email them. They are lonely, isolated, dangerous men, 
desperately seeking connections in cyberspace and beyond. They'll likely 
respond. Maybe even show up on your birthday and do balloon sculptures.

WHAT IS PUKE & SNOT?
It's a comedy act. Seriously.

WHERE DID THE NAME COME FROM?
All the good ones were taken. Truthfully, check out the 60's Broadway hit 
BEYOND THE FRINGE, written and performed by Peter Cooke, Dudley Moore, 
Alan Bennett and one other guy. The answer is in one of the sketches in that 
satirical revue.

DO THEY DO THIS FOR A LIVING?
No, they do it for the art. What kind of a stupid question is that?

CAN I HIRE THEM FOR MY EVENT?
You're too kind. You're too generous. You're too far away, you'll have to fly 
them in. Sure, if it doesn't interfere with their regular golf outings, they'll be 
there.

HAVE THEY EVER WORKED WITH ANY FAMOUS ACTORS?
Have you heard of Tom Hanks? Clint Eastwood? Julia Roberts? Jennifer 
Aniston? Well, so have they.

ARE THEY REALLY ACTORS?
OK, now you're pissing them off. This interview is over.
